Damien Prieur
CS 283
find replace prefix

Description: Create a find replace prefix program
Program searches all txt files in current dir
For each file searches for occurences of the 'find' parameter and replaces them with the 'replace' parameter
If no occurrences of the 'find' parameter then the program searches for the 'prefix' parameter
For any 'prefix' found program, the program prepends the 'find' parameter to the left of the occurrence 
If there are not 'prefix' occurrences then nothing happens to the file
Any edits to files are logged to stdout with what happened and what line it occurred on

Compiler: gcc version 7.3.0 (Ubuntu 7.3.0-27ubuntu1~18.04)
OS: Linux tux5 4.15.0-43-generic #46-Ubuntu SMP Thu Dec 6 14:45:28 UTC 2018 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux
Computer: tux.cs.drexel.edu

Requirements:
make
./frp <find> <replace> <prefix>
(have text files in the folder)


Tests:
make test	

Review:
	Good fun, tried to do it with no temp file but going backwards in files is not supported

Improvements:
	Doing this with file descriptors would be cool	

